Description: Implements continuous-time Bayesian networks (CTBNs) with four
    order-dependent structured shrinkage priors (Hierarchical Structured,
    Bayesian LASSO, Regularised Horseshoe, and Spike-and-Slab) for modelling
    the joint trajectories of multiple long-term conditions in large-scale
    electronic health records. The package provides both a fast L-BFGS-B
    MAP + Laplace estimator and a full Stan / NUTS implementation, together
    with utilities for posterior inclusion probabilities, conditional and
    synergistic risk estimation, time-dependent AUC, and Brier scores.
    Companion code for Olaniran et al. (2026).
